text: Campylomormyrus rhynchophorus is one of fourteen species of elephantfish in the genus Campylomormyrus. This species is listed as Least Concern by the IUCN.IUCN Campylomormyrus rhynchophorus reaches a maximum length of 22 cm.Fishbase.edu.tw == Distribution == This fish is distributed throughout the Congo River basin in the countries of Cameroon, the Democratic Republic of the Congo and Angola .IUCN == References == == Further reading == * Category:Weakly electric fish Category:Mormyridae Category:Fish described in 1898
